```{r setup, message=FALSE, warning=FALSE, include=FALSE}
library(metathis)

meta() %>%
  meta_description(
    "Personal website of Paolo Varraso at New York University (NYU)"
  ) %>% 
  meta_name("github-repo" = "PaoloVarraso/paolovarraso.github.io") %>% 
  meta_viewport() %>% 
  meta_social(
    title = "Paolo Varraso",
    url = "https://paolovarraso.github.io/",
    image = "https://paolovarraso.github.io/images/index_portrait.jpg",
    image_alt = "Paolo Varraso",
    og_type = "website",
    og_author = c("Paolo Varraso")
  )
```

##### I am an Assistant Professor (*"Ricercatore in Tenure Track"*) in the Department of Economics and Finance at Tor Vergata University of Rome.  

</br>

I received my PhD in Economics from New York University in 2024. 

I am a macroeconomist with interests in the fields of macro-finance, international economics and monetary economics. 

My research focuses on the role of financial markets and intermediaries in the transmission of macroeconomic shocks and policies.

Click [here](content/cv.pdf) for my CV.

</br>

